        <div class="term-row">
          <div class="term-block">
            <div class="term-title">Isometrics (start here)</div>
            <div class="term-desc">Static holds against resistance. Immediate analgesic (pain-relieving) effect. Safe even in the painful stage. 45–60 sec holds, 3–5 sets, daily.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="term-block">
            <div class="term-title">Heavy slow resistance</div>
            <div class="term-desc">Eccentric and isotonic loading. This is where lasting structural collagen change happens. 3–4× per week with recovery days in between.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="term-block">
            <div class="term-title">Energy storage</div>
            <div class="term-desc">Walking, jogging, low-level plyometrics. The tendon must store and release energy efficiently before sport demands are added.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="term-block">
            <div class="term-title">Full return to load</div>
            <div class="term-desc">Sport-specific plyometrics and high-intensity activity. Only when all lower levels are pain-free and strength targets are met.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
