        <div class="insight-box">
          <strong>The key rule:</strong> Each step must be pain-free — or below 3/10 pain that fully settles within 24 hours — before progressing to the next. Skipping steps is the most common reason tendinopathy returns. The rate of climb through the staircase varies by person; the sequence does not.
