  <!-- Key insight -->
  <div class="key-insight">
    <div class="insight-icon">⟵⟶</div>
    <div class="insight-body">
      <div class="insight-title">The continuum moves in both directions</div>
      <div class="insight-text">Stages 1 and 2 can move backward toward normal with the right intervention — primarily progressive loading, not rest. The danger is treating a Stage 2 or 3 tendon as if it were a simple acute injury. Pain settling does not mean the tendon has recovered its capacity.</div>
